"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-lifestyle-food-2024-0726-1460780-15-french-inspired-dishes-to-make-to-celebrate-the-olympics\", \"text\": \"The Olympics 2024 kick off today in Paris, the City of Lights, and we can think of no better way to mark the occasion than with cooking up some French foodie classics.  Whether you are anxiously following Ireland's Olympic track and field team, or simply watching the gymnastics for the outfits, the experience will be even more enjoyable with a homemade tarte tatin, beef bourguignon or a simple crepe accompanying you.  Cr\\u00e8me caramel    Classic coq au vin    Nico's grilled pear tarte tatin    Wade Murphy's baked elderflower cr\\u00e8me brul\\u00e9e tart    Neven's classic beef bourguignon    Michel Roux's vegetable tart tatin    Chocolate eclairs    Tartiflette    French onion soup    Almond and raspberry frangipani tart    Mark Moriarty's ratatouille tart with halloumi    Crepe Suzette    Classic omelette    French apple tart    Karen Coakley's moules frites    Search by ingredient, chef or programme    \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"